Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.76,0:00:04.45,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Final check of internal {\i1}Kivotos{\i0} systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.45,0:00:05.48,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Communication systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.48,0:00:06.35,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Electronic systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.35,0:00:07.21,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Engine systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.21,0:00:08.74,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,All systems green.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.74,0:00:11.73,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Transferring control authority to {\i1}Kivotos{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.73,0:00:15.50,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Boost capacitor has reached \Nengine ignition threshold.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.50,0:00:17.66,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Thruster engine is idling.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.66,0:00:22.46,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kivotos{\i0} hangar entrance opening rate \Nis presently at ninety-three percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.39,0:00:27.92,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Releasing docking bolts A0 to F10.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.41,0:00:31.44,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kivotos{\i0} thruster ignition confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.44,0:00:33.37,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Output is rising.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.37,0:00:35.74,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Guidance beacon signal response is excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.33,0:00:38.85,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kivotos{\i0} following specified coordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.79,0:00:43.81,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Kivotos{\i0} can function as \Nan independent spaceship,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.08,0:00:47.57,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,but it only has standard rocket \Npropulsion, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.79,0:00:52.47,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Theoretically, it's possible for it \Nto undergo hyperspace transport
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.47,0:00:56.68,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,while docked with the {\i1}Blume{\i0} via Entangle Link.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.34,0:01:00.02,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,But this will be our first time actually doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.87,0:01:04.91,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,This is risky...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.18,0:01:06.62,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Navigation system.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.62,0:01:08.18,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Autopilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.18,0:01:10.06,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Directional transmitter system.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.06,0:01:10.81,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Check.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.51,0:01:14.07,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Avionics okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.67,0:01:20.10,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,This will be the first time someone from \NEarth has experienced an Entangle Link.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.72,0:01:25.41,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,We can't predict what effect it will have \Non the two Earth crew members.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.93,0:01:28.10,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We have no data on it whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.98,0:01:31.69,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But the captain and Akari will be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.57,0:01:34.20,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,That is what I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.15,0:01:38.17,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Is that your intuition?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.43,0:01:40.28,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.37,0:01:44.43,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,I'll trust it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.06,0:01:46.25,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.76,0:01:49.71,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,what happened to that thing they \Nwere developing on the lunar base?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.12,0:01:54.54,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,You really do know everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.99,0:01:56.06,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Lunar base?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.67,0:01:58.68,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The Planter Unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.68,0:02:00.55,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Planter Unit?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.86,0:02:05.67,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Originally, Hana was the one at \Ngreatest risk with the ark plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.21,0:02:16.03,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hana couldn't leave the {\i1}Blume{\i0} on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.21,0:02:21.28,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The ark plan would try to force the {\i1}Blume{\i0} to move
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.28,0:02:24.11,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,without regard for her safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.72,0:02:27.18,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.17,0:02:31.33,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,That risk is still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.17,0:02:35.80,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,However, they were developing \Nsomething called a Planter Unit
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.54,0:02:39.69,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,on the lunar base, where there isn't \Nmuch brain wave resonance noise,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.69,0:02:42.28,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,which would transfer Hana's brain wave resonance
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.28,0:02:45.86,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,and bioinformatics to the {\i1}Blume{\i0} externally,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.35,0:02:49.33,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,allowing it to be controlled remotely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.18,0:02:55.34,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Commander Nishikubo was developing it, \Nso that if it became necessary
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.34,0:02:59.99,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,to use the {\i1}Blume{\i0}, we could \Nminimize the risk to Hana.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.89,0:03:03.18,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.15,0:03:06.89,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I've got the captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.26,0:03:15.59,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's the Planter Unit's status?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.11,0:03:19.55,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Only Commander Nishikubo knows that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.99,0:03:24.26,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,But if there were even a one-percent \Nchance that it would work,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.26,0:03:26.64,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,he would have told you about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.05,0:03:31.52,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.09,0:03:33.73,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.50,0:03:39.28,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Pointer screwed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.61,0:03:41.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he screwed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.46,0:03:44.94,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The future of the chosen boys,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.44,0:03:47.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,humanity's hope for survival,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.14,0:03:50.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,is being cut off by the Intercept Faction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.92,0:03:52.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's how it seems to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.22,0:03:57.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But the cold sleep block is still \Naboard the {\i1}Tenkaidou{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.75,0:04:02.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Rewinding the clock to the \Nark plan is still possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.68,0:04:04.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There's still time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.50,0:04:08.76,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,But they will launch the {\i1}Blume{\i0} soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.05,0:04:11.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We cannot let that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.97,0:04:14.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It is we who will use the {\i1}Blume{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.79,0:04:16.99,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter if it gets a bit banged up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.43,0:04:20.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We must retake it, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.73,0:05:54.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Eternal life...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.36,0:05:59.36,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If I really had such a thing, what would I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.89,0:06:03.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It is truly a hard question for a \Nsnob like myself to think about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.55,0:06:08.23,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,For example, whatever it is you enjoy most today,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.23,0:06:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,like that delicious wine...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.39,0:06:14.31,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,What must you do to enjoy it forever?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.63,0:06:20.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Or how to enjoy time with beautiful ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.77,0:06:23.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I think that is what I would think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.56,0:06:26.98,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,To consider it a bit more realistically,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.98,0:06:30.31,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,in my case, if I were to live for eternity...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.31,0:06:34.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I may be a little irritated by the \Nsize of the world I have to live in,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.56,0:06:39.29,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and the fact that there are still \Nso many things I do not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.29,0:06:40.40,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.40,0:06:42.58,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,First, I'd be irritated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.85,0:06:47.16,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This may not be the answer you're \Nlooking for. Please forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.79,0:06:50.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Puck does not lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.58,0:06:52.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I got that wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.01,0:06:59.44,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,As Kube Masaki, send that as my \Nanswer to Peter Westvillage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.90,0:07:01.50,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.75,0:07:05.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Amarok and the others' full-scale attack...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.85,0:07:07.43,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,...is about...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.43,0:07:09.29,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,...to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.44,0:07:10.45,Title,P,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9}The Operation Summer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.13,0:07:12.95,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.82,0:07:18.90,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Bugbear and Setsuna-sama will soon \Nreturn with the last capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.69,0:07:20.94,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's nearly time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.50,0:07:23.67,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The last night on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.54,0:07:28.87,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,The end of this planet, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.90,0:07:52.99,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,This planet wasn't that bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.08,0:07:56.03,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Nor was this avatar body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.22,0:08:02.54,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,That crêpe truck we ran together \Nwas pretty fun, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.18,0:08:05.50,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.16,0:08:13.13,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,He'd feel irritated first, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.33,0:08:19.33,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.32,0:08:23.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We're in contact with the {\i1}Kivotos{\i0}'s \Nbridge and the {\i1}Tenkaidou{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.49,0:08:30.71,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Commander, we heard about the Planter Unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.34,0:08:33.73,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Akari again?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.61,0:08:37.63,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't even close to complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.13,0:08:40.70,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The research team did their best, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.35,0:08:42.62,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.40,0:08:44.70,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.91,0:08:50.17,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that you made it because \Nyou were concerned about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.59,0:08:53.85,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You can be pretty nice sometimes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.06,0:08:57.23,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,G-Governor Yomatsuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.23,0:08:59.31,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,But it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.06,0:09:03.35,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,DEFCON 1?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.35,0:09:05.64,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, this is an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.64,0:09:08.15,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Over the last one hundred and twenty seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.15,0:09:13.08,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,the phenomenon we saw in Tokyo where \Neveryone within a given area goes into comas
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.08,0:09:15.78,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,has occurred in no fewer than twenty-five places.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.72,0:09:18.84,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,We can assume that the Planetary Gears
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.84,0:09:24.66,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,have been gathering high-density libido \Non a scale unseen up to this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.41,0:09:28.25,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,According to a report that's just come in,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.25,0:09:36.18,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Alonzo's predictive simulations suggest \Nthere's a 99.98% chance that all the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.18,0:09:41.81,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Planetary Gears on Earth will launch \Na full-scale attack in Kiltgang form.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.73,0:09:45.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,99.98%?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.81,0:09:47.90,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,A full-scale attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.90,0:09:51.36,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Seven Kiltgangs attacking at once?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.71,0:09:55.11,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And it could happen right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.13,0:09:56.78,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.88,0:10:00.59,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I understand there's no time to waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.62,0:10:07.75,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The Midsummer's Knights will now launch the \Nattack on enemy fortress carrier {\i1}Oberon{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.01,0:10:10.27,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,in orbit around Uranus.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.91,0:10:20.39,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Protect the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.76,0:10:22.05,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.54,0:10:25.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They can do this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.52,0:10:26.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.17,0:10:29.73,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go swimming again, Teppei-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.23,0:10:31.39,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.39,0:10:32.94,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be back, Governor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.54,0:10:35.58,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.04,0:10:42.70,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be back, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.62,0:10:47.71,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.88,0:10:49.58,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.46,0:10:51.86,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,take care of Akari.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.78,0:10:53.37,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.70,0:10:57.98,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Wipe out the enemy, and come back safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.40,0:11:00.26,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the terms of success for this mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.81,0:11:01.82,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.82,0:11:02.71,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.80,0:11:04.59,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.29,0:11:08.89,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The anniversary of Taiyou's death is in a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.77,0:11:11.44,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go visit his grave together.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.23,0:11:15.86,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.49,0:11:17.53,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,For sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.26,0:11:20.49,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,It's a promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.90,0:11:25.36,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,They're the team we hoped for.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.43,0:11:28.12,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.81,0:11:30.81,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.40,0:11:36.25,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, you heard the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.16,0:11:39.02,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,At this very moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.02,0:11:44.93,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,the enemy might launch an attack \Nwith seven Kiltgangs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.55,0:11:50.43,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Our ship, the {\i1}Blume{\i0}, will head \Nfor the fortress carrier {\i1}Oberon{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.43,0:11:52.02,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,in orbit around Uranus.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.32,0:11:54.81,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,If I concentrate on the Entangle Link,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.81,0:12:00.12,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I can't use the {\i1}Blume{\i0}'s normal weapons \Nor change our course at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.12,0:12:01.65,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.65,0:12:03.45,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We'll protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.83,0:12:06.18,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.63,0:12:10.44,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.31,0:12:12.71,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to the {\i1}Blume{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.89,0:12:16.40,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hana, are you sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.83,0:12:24.55,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.43,0:12:28.31,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,When this mission is over,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.83,0:12:33.16,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,let's go to a festival and eat \Na candy apple together!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.37,0:12:36.27,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.18,0:12:39.82,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.22,0:12:49.49,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,When you destroyed that debris back there,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.11,0:12:52.95,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I thought to myself that you've \Nbecome a real captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.54,0:12:58.67,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You should have it, as proof \Nthat you're the captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.37,0:13:02.11,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be a real captain
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.37,0:13:05.73,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,when this mission is successfully completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.51,0:13:08.30,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Until then, keep it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.73,0:13:10.56,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.84,0:13:19.70,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hana, can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.48,0:13:21.27,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.79,0:13:25.54,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Can you use your Livlaster?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.37,0:13:27.26,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.05,0:13:33.12,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starting up the main engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.39,0:13:36.33,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll let you handle the timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.26,0:13:40.13,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Let's save the Earth together, partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.62,0:13:43.84,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Leave it to me, partner!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.80,0:13:59.23,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like they're attacking \Nwith the {\i1}Blume{\i0}, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.23,0:14:02.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They have the {\i1}Blume{\i0} and the Livlaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.72,0:14:06.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Ai's failure with that debris plan hurt us a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.24,0:14:06.97,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.97,0:14:08.53,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,It's all my fault?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.12,0:14:15.00,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Does Albion really intend to destroy \Nthe cocoon and all our Ego Blocks?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.55,0:14:17.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.05,0:14:23.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Does Albion intend to die here, \Nin this solar system?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.22,0:14:29.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If the cocoon is destroyed, we won't \Nbe able to go to other systems
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.43,0:14:31.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,after eating all the Earthlings' libido energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.93,0:14:36.67,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But it appears they're bringing \Ntheir usual group of friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.67,0:14:39.06,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi Manatsu and Akari Yomatsuri, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.23,0:14:46.03,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If their minds can handle the Entangle Link, \Nit's possible that they'd take them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.28,0:14:50.99,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, having a Neoteny around would be helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.20,0:14:57.84,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I can't imagine an Earthling being able to \Nwithstand an Entangle Link's hyperspace transport.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.30,0:15:02.26,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Their weak minds are less than human.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.26,0:15:04.34,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,How arrogant are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.95,0:15:07.30,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.30,0:15:10.52,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,This will be good fun before our attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.47,0:15:19.89,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,An Impacter has appeared in front of the {\i1}Blume{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.24,0:15:21.47,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Omega sector.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.47,0:15:22.48,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Distance: 150,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.80,0:15:24.19,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,An Impacter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.19,0:15:26.81,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,The Garm Engine...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.42,0:15:33.29,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,A massive Impacter developed by the \NArk Faction to capture the Kiltgangs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.84,0:15:35.62,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It must be Salty Dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.41,0:15:37.67,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,At a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.33,0:15:40.87,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't we tell you we'd protect you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.29,0:15:44.41,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You concentrate on the Entangle Link.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.78,0:15:46.59,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.93,0:15:48.28,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei, Akari...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.28,0:15:49.17,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.17,0:15:50.03,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.52,0:15:53.42,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,We will now begin Operation Summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.95,0:16:27.63,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,In terms of size, that monster's \Nas big as the {\i1}Tenkaidou{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.12,0:16:30.48,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's entering our firing range, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.22,0:16:35.05,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Mid-sized Impacters are splitting \Noff from the Garm Engine!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.86,0:16:38.01,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's Cerberus!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.01,0:16:39.22,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Cerberus?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.73,0:16:43.83,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'll head out in the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.83,0:16:45.45,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of the ship, Teppei.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.45,0:16:46.90,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You understand, don't you, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.31,0:16:53.06,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,If something happens to you, \NHana won't be able to leave the {\i1}Blume{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.26,0:16:55.89,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.17,0:17:11.96,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,A beam cannon?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.74,0:17:44.75,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The Earth Engine has left the \Nship and engaged Cerberus.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.26,0:17:46.96,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,It's leaving the {\i1}Blume{\i0} behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.31,0:17:50.04,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Blume{\i0} has engaged the Garm Engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.82,0:18:04.86,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,That's the Livlaster DC's barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.01,0:18:07.31,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.31,0:18:09.23,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,He can use it from the {\i1}Kivotos{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.90,0:18:25.41,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we can't damage it from long range.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.83,0:18:29.74,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It'll hurt us, not being able to \Nuse the {\i1}Blume{\i0}'s weapons...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.41,0:18:31.38,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.59,0:18:47.18,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,Form a strong image in your mind \Nof the place you want to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.84,0:19:14.70,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I can see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.15,0:19:32.03,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Akari,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.62,0:19:33.73,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,it's connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.34,0:19:35.41,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,We can jump soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.41,0:19:36.57,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.57,0:19:38.19,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, you heard that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.78,0:19:43.01,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The Entangle Link will begin soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.01,0:19:43.87,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.72,0:19:48.16,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That stupid kid thinks he's a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.53,0:19:56.72,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't interfere with our plan to save humanity!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.55,0:20:03.39,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you interfering?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.06,0:20:11.60,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,This mission is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.06,0:20:14.51,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,to save Earth!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.87,0:20:30.89,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We're entering the Entangle Link?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.89,0:20:33.44,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,But the captain isn't back yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.44,0:20:34.57,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.57,0:20:35.38,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hana?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.13,0:20:38.35,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.37,0:20:41.46,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I can't control it anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.91,0:20:44.67,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.70,0:20:53.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let them escape, Garm!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.13,0:21:15.88,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.86,0:21:20.71,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,When this mission is over,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.30,0:21:25.49,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,let's go to a festival and eat \Na candy apple together!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.61,0:21:28.74,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.74,0:21:29.80,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,it's a promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.15,0:21:48.14,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Get there!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.08,0:21:58.83,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.81,0:22:01.21,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I can't dodge it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.29,0:22:29.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.46,0:22:31.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Time to get up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.65,0:22:33.57,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.67,0:22:42.56,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,A dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.71,0:24:15.43,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I woke up to find myself in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.05,0:24:17.39,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Daichi Manatsu,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.39,0:24:18.97,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,a second-year high school student.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.97,0:24:20.73,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,And summer break starts tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.01,0:24:22.27,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,A normal, everyday life.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.03,0:24:24.04,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.73,0:24:28.07,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The wind in this town feels wrong, somehow...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.54,0:24:32.11,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,And I keep thinking about the \Ndream I had last night,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.11,0:24:33.74,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,but I can't remember it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.06,0:24:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, on episode 23 of {\i1}Captain Earth{\i0}:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.12,0:24:39.20,Title2,,0000,0000,0000,,A Midsummer Night's Dream
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.60,0:24:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Midsummer Night's Dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.52,0:24:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Engine... What's that, again?
